			<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"http:\/\/schema.org","@type":"Recipe","name":"Easy Moist Cornbread Recipe","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Baker Bettie"},"datePublished":"2018-10-08","recipeYield":8,"description":"This easy and moist cornbread recipe is a true southern treat made with tangy buttermilk and cooked in a cast iron skillet to achieve the iconic crispy bottom. This one bowl recipe is incredibly versatile and is a great base recipe to create endless variations!\u00a0","image":["https:\/\/bakerbettie.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/moist-cornbread-recipe4-720x720.jpg","https:\/\/bakerbettie.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/moist-cornbread-recipe4-720x540.jpg","https:\/\/bakerbettie.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/moist-cornbread-recipe4.jpg","https:\/\/bakerbettie.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/moist-cornbread-recipe4-720x405.jpg","https:\/\/bakerbettie.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/moist-cornbread-recipe4-735x735.jpg"],"recipeCategory":"All Recipes","prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT20M","performTime":"PT20M","totalTime":"PT35M","recipeIngredient":["140 grams (10 tablespoons) unsalted butter, divided ","240 grams (2 cups) cornmeal (good quality stone ground cornmeal preferred)","60 grams (\u00bd cup) all-purpose flour","1 \u00bd teaspoons baking powder","\u00bd teaspoon baking soda","1 \u00be teaspoons kosher salt","25 grams (2 tablespoons) granulated sugar ","360 grams (1 \u00bd cups, 360 milliliters) buttermilk, room temperature* ","2 large eggs, room temperature"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Position an oven rack to the center position and place a well seasoned 10 inch or 12 inch (25 or 30 cm) cast iron skillet inside. Preheat the oven to 450\u00b0F\/230\u00b0C. (Preheating the skillet helps create cornbread with a crispy bottom.)","position":1,"name":"Position an oven rack to the center position...","url":"https:\/\/bakerbettie.com\/easy-moist-cornbread-recipe\/#mv_create_47_1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"While the oven and cast iron skillet preheat, melt the butter (140 grams\/ 10 tablespoons) in a saucepan on the stove or slowly in the microwave. Once completely melted, set aside about 2 tablespoons to use to grease the skillet. The remaining butter will be used in the batter. Set both aside to cool slightly.","position":2,"name":"While the oven and cast iron skillet preheat,...","url":"https:\/\/bakerbettie.com\/easy-moist-cornbread-recipe\/#mv_create_47_2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a large mixing bowl, add the cornmeal(240 grams\/ 2 cups), all-purpose flour (60 grams\/ \u00bd cup), baking powder (1 \u00bd teaspoons), baking soda (\u00bd teaspoon), salt (1 \u00be teaspoons), and sugar (25 grams\/ 2 tablespoons). Whisk together until combined.","position":3,"name":"In a large mixing bowl, add the cornmeal(240...","url":"https:\/\/bakerbettie.com\/easy-moist-cornbread-recipe\/#mv_create_47_3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add in the buttermilk (360 grams\/ 1 \u00bd cups), eggs (2 large), and the larger amount of melted butter (8 tablespoons). Stir until everything is just incorporated- try not to over-mix.","position":4,"name":"Add in the buttermilk (360 grams\/ 1 \u00bd...","url":"https:\/\/bakerbettie.com\/easy-moist-cornbread-recipe\/#mv_create_47_4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Carefully remove the hot cast iron skillet from the oven. Add the remaining melted butter (about 2 tablespoons) to the skillet and swirl it around until the bottom is coated. Pour the cornbread batter into the skillet and immediately place the skillet back into the hot oven.","position":5,"name":"Carefully remove the hot cast iron skillet from...","url":"https:\/\/bakerbettie.com\/easy-moist-cornbread-recipe\/#mv_create_47_5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Bake for 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with moist crumbs. For a crispier top, put it under the broiler for 1-2 minutes, watching it very closely.","position":6,"name":"Bake for 20 minutes or until a toothpick...","url":"https:\/\/bakerbettie.com\/easy-moist-cornbread-recipe\/#mv_create_47_6"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Optional: Run a stick of butter over the top of the baked cornbread while it is still hot. The butter will seep into the bread and keep it extra moist and flavorfulnd keep it extra moist and delicious.","position":7,"name":"Optional: Run a stick of butter over the...","url":"https:\/\/bakerbettie.com\/easy-moist-cornbread-recipe\/#mv_create_47_7"}],"video":{"@type":"VideoObject","name":"Easy Moist Cornbread","description":"This easy and moist cornbread recipe is a true southern treat made with tangy buttermilk and cooked in a cast iron skillet to achieve that iconic crispy bottom. This one bowl recipe is incredibly versatile and is a great base recipe to create endless variations!","thumbnailUrl":["https:\/\/images.scriptwrapper.com\/cdn-cgi\/image\/fit=contain\/https:\/\/thumbnails.scriptwrapper.com\/786\/zzebuqyaraussciikhsu","https:\/\/images.scriptwrapper.com\/cdn-cgi\/image\/fit=contain\/https:\/\/thumbnails.scriptwrapper.com\/786\/zzebuqyaraussciikhsu","https:\/\/images.scriptwrapper.com\/cdn-cgi\/image\/fit=contain\/https:\/\/thumbnails.scriptwrapper.com\/786\/zzebuqyaraussciikhsu"],"contentUrl":"https:\/\/mediavine-res.cloudinary.com\/video\/upload\/csbxd7rv3mdlzovawlcg.mp4","duration":"PT137S","uploadDate":"2023-02-08T17:39:14+00:00"},"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":4.4,"reviewCount":"420"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2026-01-25T16:00:15+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2026-01-03T22:10:28+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2026-01-01T23:08:46+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-12-28T22:57:03+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-12-28T17:25:22+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-11-28T17:11:59+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-11-27T11:26:26+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-11-27T05:44:32+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-11-26T18:59:14+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-10-18T19:19:58+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-10-17T22:29:27+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-10-15T19:46:53+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-09-11T11:43:20+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Stephen B"},"datePublished":"2025-08-23T15:42:33+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"},"reviewBody":"I followed standard high altitude rules : increase liquid and reduce leavening. So 2 cups of buttermilk and only one tsp of baking powder. \u00a0I also used honey not sugar.\u00a0\nThe result was spectacular. \u00a0The butter and honey led to a great light brown crust.\u00a0\nThis cornbread is so easy and fast, it's a great high altitude bread.\u00a0","name":"Great result (at 10,000 feet)"},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Mike T"},"datePublished":"2025-08-15T02:14:38+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"2.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"},"reviewBody":"Sorry dude, yours did not compare.","name":"Southern Style was better"},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-07-31T23:33:36+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-06-14T20:57:13+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-05-27T22:18:09+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-05-27T19:50:53+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anonymous"},"datePublished":"2025-05-15T23:26:27+00:00","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4.0","bestRating":"5","worstRating":"1"}},{"@type":"Review","au