		<ol id="comment-list" class="comment-list">
			
		<h3 id="comment-title">
			167 Comments on &ldquo;Easy Moist Cornbread&rdquo;		</h3>
		
				    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-544499">
	        <div id="comment-544499" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Kyle</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2021-12-04T18:04:10-04:00">
                December 4, 2021 @ 6:04 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-544499" data-commentid="544499" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-544499" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kyle" aria-label="Reply to Kyle">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>450 is way too hot to be cooking this for 20min.  I just did it and it burnt my cornbread.  Either turn the temp down or decrease the cook time.  You can always leave it in a little longer but you can’t come back from a ruined loaf. </p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-544555">
	        <div id="comment-544555" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2021-12-06T11:55:51-04:00">
                December 6, 2021 @ 11:55 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-544555" data-commentid="544555" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-544555" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Oh no, I&#8217;m so sorry! I wonder if your oven is a bit too hot. Do you have an oven thermometer? This recipe has been tested many times with great results. What kind of pan are you using?</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even depth-2" id="li-comment-564671">
	        <div id="comment-564671" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Emma</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-01-01T13:54:39-04:00">
                January 1, 2023 @ 1:54 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-564671" data-commentid="564671" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-564671" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Emma" aria-label="Reply to Emma">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I&#8217;d drop to 425. I took mine out (450 like recipe) and it was super brown. I think 2 more minutes would have crossed over todl the burnt taste. I also am curious about other recipes that heat the skillet 425 add the butter same as here, but after adding the batter turn down to 350 and bake longer.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment odd alt depth-3" id="li-comment-586613">
	        <div id="comment-586613" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Jean Smith</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2024-10-14T16:41:16-04:00">
                October 14, 2024 @ 4:41 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-586613" data-commentid="586613" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-586613" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jean Smith" aria-label="Reply to Jean Smith">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Mine was perfect at 450 for 20 minutes.  Thinking it must be differences in oven heat or pan like the chef suggests</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even depth-2" id="li-comment-578391">
	        <div id="comment-578391" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Doris</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2024-04-28T10:26:36-04:00">
                April 28, 2024 @ 10:26 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-578391" data-commentid="578391" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-578391" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Doris" aria-label="Reply to Doris">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Very true&#8230;. 400 degrees is enough heat.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-544721">
	        <div id="comment-544721" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Denise</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2021-12-11T10:13:53-04:00">
                December 11, 2021 @ 10:13 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-544721" data-commentid="544721" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-544721" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Denise" aria-label="Reply to Denise">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Good morning and Merry Christmas! I LOVE your recipes! I was wondering if I could use gluten free flour on your corn bread recipe??</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment even depth-2" id="li-comment-550665">
	        <div id="comment-550665" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Laurie</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-03-23T15:35:12-04:00">
                March 23, 2022 @ 3:35 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-550665" data-commentid="550665" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-550665" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Laurie" aria-label="Reply to Laurie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I’ve used bobs red mill 1:1 for many recipes </p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-545048">
	        <div id="comment-545048" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Shakerah</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2021-12-16T12:17:15-04:00">
                December 16, 2021 @ 12:17 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-545048" data-commentid="545048" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-545048" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Shakerah" aria-label="Reply to Shakerah">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>This is a tried and tested recipe for real. I&#8217;m so happy to have found it. I don&#8217;t usually add baking soda but it makes a world of difference and the tip for making buttermilk was great. This will be my go to recipe from now on.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-545262">
	        <div id="comment-545262" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2021-12-20T12:52:43-04:00">
                December 20, 2021 @ 12:52 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-545262" data-commentid="545262" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-545262" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Im so glad you enjoy it!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-546414">
	        <div id="comment-546414" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Rosa</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2021-12-29T18:24:47-04:00">
                December 29, 2021 @ 6:24 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-546414" data-commentid="546414" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-546414" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Rosa" aria-label="Reply to Rosa">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Hi  @bakerbettie,<br />
Thank you for this recipe! My mom loves corn bread, muffins, on the cobb, basically anything corn.  <br />
I just added 1 tsp of salt, added one cup of flour (by mistake) and baked at 420 instead of 450 degrees. It turned out great!  Very soft and crunchy around the  edges </p>
<p>I have photos, but not sure how to send them. </p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-547146">
	        <div id="comment-547146" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-01-03T16:41:41-04:00">
                January 3, 2022 @ 4:41 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-547146" data-commentid="547146" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-547146" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
