	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-548936">
	        <div id="comment-548936" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Charlie</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-02-14T13:50:02-04:00">
                February 14, 2022 @ 1:50 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-548936" data-commentid="548936" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-548936" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Charlie" aria-label="Reply to Charlie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I love this recipe! I make it all of the time! The one thing I&#8217;d like to note is that you stated that 2 cups of cornmeal is 240 grams. That&#8217;s accurate for wheat flour, but looking at my back of Bob&#8217;s Red Mill Medium Grind Cornmeal, 2 cups end up being 304 grams.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-548937">
	        <div id="comment-548937" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-02-14T14:10:41-04:00">
                February 14, 2022 @ 2:10 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-548937" data-commentid="548937" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-548937" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>thanks for your feedback!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-549903">
	        <div id="comment-549903" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Judy Johnston</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-03-09T08:20:59-04:00">
                March 9, 2022 @ 8:20 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-549903" data-commentid="549903" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-549903" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Judy Johnston" aria-label="Reply to Judy Johnston">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I am an old Southern cook, but I&#8217;ve never mastered cornbread. </p>
<p>It&#8217;s a long story.</p>
<p>This is the first recipe for cornbread I&#8217;ve ever tried that turned out perfectly. </p>
<p>Thank you!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
