                April 4, 2022 @ 4:39 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-551113" data-commentid="551113" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-551113" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Krista" aria-label="Reply to Krista">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Make sure you use unsalted butter and you level off your teaspoons!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment odd alt depth-3" id="li-comment-565084">
	        <div id="comment-565084" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Marie Crawford</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-01-23T21:16:39-04:00">
                January 23, 2023 @ 9:16 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-565084" data-commentid="565084" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-565084" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Marie Crawford" aria-label="Reply to Marie Crawford">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Same here &#8211; way too salty.  I used unsalted butter and 2 level teaspoons of Morton kosher salt. Maybe you are using another brand.  Other than that, fantastic recipe!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment even depth-4" id="li-comment-575911">
	        <div id="comment-575911" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>LILY B</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-12-26T00:47:33-04:00">
                December 26, 2023 @ 12:47 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-575911" data-commentid="575911" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-575911" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to LILY B" aria-label="Reply to LILY B">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>This happens if you use sea salt or a specialty salt.  so because I use sea salt, I reduced the amount of salt the next times and it was great! BEST CORNBREAD EVER!! It&#8217;s a hit with family and friends.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-550149">
	        <div id="comment-550149" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Steve</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-03-13T17:52:48-04:00">
                March 13, 2022 @ 5:52 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-550149" data-commentid="550149" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-550149" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Steve" aria-label="Reply to Steve">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>If I am using pre-cooked cornmeal would the recipe need to be adjusted?</p>
<p>Thanks!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-550232">
	        <div id="comment-550232" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-03-15T11:35:06-04:00">
                March 15, 2022 @ 11:35 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-550232" data-commentid="550232" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-550232" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I think you would need to find a recipe that specifically calls for that. I&#8217;m not sure how it work out with this one.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
