</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-553688">
	        <div id="comment-553688" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>David Wolrath</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-05-24T22:20:25-04:00">
                May 24, 2022 @ 10:20 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-553688" data-commentid="553688" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-553688" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to David Wolrath" aria-label="Reply to David Wolrath">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I don&#8217;t usually leave comments, but I just made this and it was great! Every bit as good as Marie Calendar&#8217;s cornbread! My wife loved it!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-554212">
	        <div id="comment-554212" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-05-31T12:12:30-04:00">
                May 31, 2022 @ 12:12 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-554212" data-commentid="554212" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-554212" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I&#8217;m so glad!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-556808">
	        <div id="comment-556808" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Laura</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-07-01T21:09:37-04:00">
                July 1, 2022 @ 9:09 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-556808" data-commentid="556808" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-556808" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Laura" aria-label="Reply to Laura">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I know it&#8217;s summer, but had to make a skillet of this to go with some beans. Used Bob&#8217;s Red Mill gluten-free 1:1, vegan butter, 3 eggs vs 2, and soy milk+1T vinegar for buttermilk (very finicky diets around here). The cast-iron pan I have is high-sided but it baked up beautifully. Baked 450F convection with no adjustment to temp. Did not burn. Nice browning on top. I&#8217;ve had a little bite and it is moist, not sweet. Could be a keeper!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-557378">
	        <div id="comment-557378" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Sara</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-07-07T21:52:40-04:00">
                July 7, 2022 @ 9:52 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-557378" data-commentid="557378" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-557378" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sara" aria-label="Reply to Sara">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I used 2 teaspoons salt (leveled off) and unsalted butter, and it was WAY too salty. Practically inedible. Frankly, I had to throw it out. If I do make this again, I&#8217;m only going to use 1 teaspoon.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-560790">
	        <div id="comment-560790" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Aaron</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-09-05T00:53:30-04:00">
                September 5, 2022 @ 12:53 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-560790" data-commentid="560790" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-560790" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Aaron" aria-label="Reply to Aaron">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I keep trying others and I keep coming back to this cornbread recipe. Every time I say, &#8220;now THAT is cornbread.&#8221;</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-560887">
	        <div id="comment-560887" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-09-06T12:27:46-04:00">
                September 6, 2022 @ 12:27 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-560887" data-commentid="560887" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-560887" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>So glad you like it!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-563418">
	        <div id="comment-563418" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Ms. TrulyTasteful</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-11-03T12:56:59-04:00">
                November 3, 2022 @ 12:56 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-563418" data-commentid="563418" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-563418" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Ms. TrulyTasteful" aria-label="Reply to Ms. TrulyTasteful">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Tried this recipe a few times in my old cast iron skillet and it tastes as good as my Ma-ma&#8217;s [my grandmother&#8217;s] recipe. Hers was AUTHENTIC southern cornbread from the farm at the Louisiana &#8211; Arkansas border with bacon drippings on top before baking.<br />
Love the research done about the history of corn used in cornbread and how our current practices change the flavor of the cornbread we produce today.<br />
THANK YOU, Bettie! I&#8217;m a big fan of your exacting research and testing standards!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-563637">
	        <div id="comment-563637" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>AB</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-11-10T13:50:18-04:00">
                November 10, 2022 @ 1:50 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-563637" data-commentid="563637" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-563637" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to AB" aria-label="Reply to AB">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I have a 15&#8243; cast iron and I was thinking I would double the recipe; do you think that would be okay?</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-563728">
	        <div id="comment-563728" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-11-14T14:40:06-04:00">
                November 14, 2022 @ 2:40 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-563728" data-commentid="563728" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-563728" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I don&#8217;t think that will be big enough. You might only fit about 3/4 of the batter.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-606081">
	        <div id="comment-606081" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Beth Hoppes</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2025-09-15T08:02:50-04:00">
                September 15, 2025 @ 8:02 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-606081" data-commentid="606081" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-606081" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Beth Hoppes" aria-label="Reply to Beth Hoppes">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>A 15&#8243; skillet actually has 2.3x the area of a 10&#8243;, &amp; 1.5x the area of a 12&#8243; skillet. So, doubling it should be fine. I assume you would just need to cook it a bit longer.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-564637">
	        <div id="comment-564637" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Gwena</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2022-12-30T14:54:11-04:00">
                December 30, 2022 @ 2:54 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-564637" data-commentid="564637" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-564637" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Gwena" aria-label="Reply to Gwena">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Can you use self rising meal in their recipe.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-564803">
	        <div id="comment-564803" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Donna Nordman</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-01-08T13:17:05-04:00">
                January 8, 2023 @ 1:17 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-564803" data-commentid="564803" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-564803" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Donna Nordman" aria-label="Reply to Donna Nordman">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>This recipe produced a perfect cornbread!  There&#8217;s nothing like a cast iron skillet to bring this dish to life&#8230;.crispy on the outside and moist on the inside.  Thanks for sharing!!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-564817">
	        <div id="comment-564817" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-01-09T15:40:44-04:00">
                January 9, 2023 @ 3:40 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-564817" data-commentid="564817" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-564817" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>So glad you liked it! And I agree 😉</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-564897">
	        <div id="comment-564897" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Ashley Brown</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-01-14T21:59:27-04:00">
                January 14, 2023 @ 9:59 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-564897" data-commentid="564897" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-564897" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Ashley Brown" aria-label="Reply to Ashley Brown">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I am great at making cornbread! True southern gal here, &amp; definitely an iron skillet is the way to go! THIS CORNBREAD TOPS IT ALL! For those that say, it’s too salty year to buttery or whatever they’re probably just not true southerners, lol! I just wanna tell you that my family is in love with this cornbread and that’s all I make anymore when I make cornbread! Job well done this recipe is absolutely hands-down OUT OF THIS WORLD AH-MAAA-ZING!! Thank you so much! </p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-565073">
	        <div id="comment-565073" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-01-23T15:35:27-04:00">
                January 23, 2023 @ 3:35 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-565073" data-commentid="565073" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-565073" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Thanks so much for the kind review! I&#8217;m so happy you like it!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-565321">
	        <div id="comment-565321" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Leah</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-02-05T02:52:55-04:00">
                February 5, 2023 @ 2:52 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-565321" data-commentid="565321" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-565321" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Leah" aria-label="Reply to Leah">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>It was excellent, I added a chopped up jalapeno and some corn niblets to it. So quick and satisfying. For those who commented that it was too salty, I think they might not know the difference between kosher salt and table salt as I used kosher salt (and unsalted butter) and it was just right. If you are using regular salt you would use half the amount.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-565443">
	        <div id="comment-565443" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Lenora W</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-02-09T16:16:28-04:00">
                February 9, 2023 @ 4:16 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-565443" data-commentid="565443" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-565443" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lenora W" aria-label="Reply to Lenora W">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>It depends on what part of the South you are from that decides if you&#8217;ll be eating white or yellow cornbread. I am from Louisiana and never had white cornbread until i moved to Georgia. White cornbread is most served here but I have had yellow served to me in restaurants too. I have had yellow cornbread served sweet and not sweet. I love all versions of this Southern staple, white or yellow. I make all of them intermittently, depending on what  meal I am serving.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-565553">
	        <div id="comment-565553" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-02-13T14:06:19-04:00">
                February 13, 2023 @ 2:06 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-565553" data-commentid="565553" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-565553" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>That&#8217;s so interesting! Thanks for sharing!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-565530">
	        <div id="comment-565530" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>sue pennock</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-02-12T19:53:25-04:00">
                February 12, 2023 @ 7:53 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-565530" data-commentid="565530" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-565530" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to sue pennock" aria-label="Reply to sue pennock">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I think the problem might be its says to preheat oven at 450. But it should be baked<br />
400.  I just used less table salt 1 teas. Thanks</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-565549">
	        <div id="comment-565549" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-02-13T13:59:24-04:00">
                February 13, 2023 @ 1:59 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-565549" data-commentid="565549" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-565549" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>If using a cast iron skillet it should be baked a 450F. If you&#8217;re using a baking pan other than a skillet then you should bake at 400F.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-565568">
	        <div id="comment-565568" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Tyanne</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-02-14T02:55:44-04:00">
                February 14, 2023 @ 2:55 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-565568" data-commentid="565568" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-565568" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Tyanne" aria-label="Reply to Tyanne">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>In my country, we don&#8217;t do cornbread. It&#8217;s not part of our culture. But I really needed to find a recipe to make some Chili Cornbread Casserole for my American boyfriend and I decided to try this one first. Since I don&#8217;t know what &#8220;Kosher&#8221; salt means, and that I wouldn&#8217;t want to use that anyway, and given the comments I read about the cornbread being too salty, I chose to add 1 single teaspoon of table salt. I used a round, basic baking pan. Other than that, I strictly followed each step of the recipe and did exactly as instructed. I decided to leave my oven at 230°C and baked the cornbread for 15 to 20 minutes. The result clearly exceeded my expectations. The cornbread looked exactly like the photos posted on this page, the taste and texture were absolutely divine, not too salty, moist and just perfect. My first cornbread ever was a success and I don&#8217;t need any other recipe. This is the one I&#8217;m going to keep for years to come. No need to say the Chili Cornbread Casserole reached levels of scrumptiousness never reached before. I am super pleased!!!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-567687">
	        <div id="comment-567687" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Kristopher</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-05-14T18:13:11-04:00">
                May 14, 2023 @ 6:13 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-567687" data-commentid="567687" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-567687" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kristopher" aria-label="Reply to Kristopher">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Made this tonight &amp; paired it with Baby back ribs &amp; mashed potatoes. Followed everything but used only 1 teaspoon of salt as it was regular table salt. Not at all to salty. Will experiment next time with more sugar to be a little more sweeter. Great recipe overall.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-569138">
	        <div id="comment-569138" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-07-18T15:07:41-04:00">
                July 18, 2023 @ 3:07 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-569138" data-commentid="569138" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-569138" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Wonderful! Ribs, mashed potatoes, and cornbread sounds PERFECT!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-574490">
	        <div id="comment-574490" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Daniel</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-10-08T10:39:34-04:00">
                October 8, 2023 @ 10:39 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-574490" data-commentid="574490" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-574490" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Daniel" aria-label="Reply to Daniel">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Great recipe!  Thanks.  <br />
I put in 2 cobs worth of raw freshly-shucked sweet  corn, 2 diced jalapeños from my garden, 2 cups of dried corn and  60 grams of Red Fife wheat berries both of which I milled at home ( right before I started) and a cup of grated organic pepper jack cheese.  I also decreased the butter to 8 tablespoons and the sugar to 1 tablespoon.   Obviously, I did things my way, but the base cornbread recipe is very good.   Thanks again!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-575083">
	        <div id="comment-575083" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Deila</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2023-11-11T17:23:51-04:00">
                November 11, 2023 @ 5:23 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-575083" data-commentid="575083" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-575083" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Deila" aria-label="Reply to Deila">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Hi. I have had your recipe pinned for a couple years now and have always enjoyed the product.  It seems this is a new version as the  previous included honey? Would it be possible to share that one please?</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-576103">
	        <div id="comment-576103" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Janet and Olin THOMAS</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2024-01-04T16:50:15-04:00">
                January 4, 2024 @ 4:50 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-576103" data-commentid="576103" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-576103" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Janet and Olin THOMAS" aria-label="Reply to Janet and Olin THOMAS">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Made a pan of corn bread using this recipe and yellow corn meal we ground ourselves. Wow! it was really good. It rose good, browned really well, and was really moist it went good with fried pork chop, fresh turnip greens, and baked sweet potato. We plan to eat leftover cornbread with the pot of venison chili tonight.  I can&#8217;t wait to make this recipe using cornmeal made from some of the Jimmy Red corn we grew this year! Thank You!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-577044">
	        <div id="comment-577044" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Wannabe Cook</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2024-02-19T11:46:33-04:00">
                February 19, 2024 @ 11:46 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-577044" data-commentid="577044" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-577044" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Wannabe Cook" aria-label="Reply to Wannabe Cook">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Made this last night and followed recipe to the letter except for the un-salted butter (didn&#8217;t realize I grabbed the wrong one).  Cornbread was good except slightly salty as expected due to the butter. Only other issue was it was drier than I had expected but after reading some comments here, I may try it again at 425. </p>
<p>Also, If I wanted to add yellow cake mix would I substitute it for the flour? I have no culinary or baking education except trial and error so not sure on the substitution possibilities.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-577045">
	        <div id="comment-577045" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2024-02-19T13:37:21-04:00">
                February 19, 2024 @ 1:37 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-577045" data-commentid="577045" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-577045" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Hi, if you have an oven thermometer I would check your oven just in case it&#8217;s slightly off (they usually are a little bit at least). I also like to run a stick of butter over the top after it comes out of the oven. It runs down and keeps the cornbread moist. I don&#8217;t suggest adding yellow cake mix- are you trying to make a cake? I would follow the directions on the mix for that.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-577855">
	        <div id="comment-577855" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Betty Cooper</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2024-03-25T16:11:16-04:00">
                March 25, 2024 @ 4:11 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-577855" data-commentid="577855" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-577855" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Betty Cooper" aria-label="Reply to Betty Cooper">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Wow, I am way over 70 years old and have finally found the perfect cornbread recipe. I have made it twice this week already and it is a hit !  Thank you Bettie !</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-578181">
	        <div id="comment-578181" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2024-04-16T12:49:19-04:00">
                April 16, 2024 @ 12:49 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-578181" data-commentid="578181" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-578181" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>You&#8217;re welcome, enjoy!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-585811">
	        <div id="comment-585811" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Kennya</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2024-09-25T21:31:43-04:00">
                September 25, 2024 @ 9:31 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-585811" data-commentid="585811" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-585811" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kennya" aria-label="Reply to Kennya">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>OMG. I didn’t even know I liked cornbread! I didn’t have buttermilk so I replaced it with full fat yogurt and heavy cream to give it some tang that buttermilk would have had. Not sure if this is why it was so dang moist and delicious but it really was. I also only used one teaspoon of salt. And I also used a scale for the dry ingredients. </p>
<p>So so good. Had some warm out of the oven with honey…. So delicious </p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-586498">
	        <div id="comment-586498" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Nonamous</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2024-10-12T14:22:00-04:00">
                October 12, 2024 @ 2:22 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-586498" data-commentid="586498" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-586498" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Nonamous" aria-label="Reply to Nonamous">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I hope this emoji means I find this cornbread so delicious, I&#8217;m drooling! Yum!</p>
<p>You forgot to say yalla corn meal not white. That&#8217;s yellow for all ya non southanas. It ain&#8217;t the butta that makes it yalla!</p>
<p>White corn bread is a mystery to me. Maybe it goes with Navy beans. Lol.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-588141">
	        <div id="comment-588141" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Melissa</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2024-11-24T00:46:44-04:00">
                November 24, 2024 @ 12:46 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-588141" data-commentid="588141" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-588141" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Melissa" aria-label="Reply to Melissa">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Delicious!  Even my husband, who does not eat cornbread, liked it. <br />
I made it with fresh ground corn just as the recipe is written and it turned out great!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-588449">
	        <div id="comment-588449" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Linda</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2024-12-01T17:40:02-04:00">
                December 1, 2024 @ 5:40 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-588449" data-commentid="588449" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-588449" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Linda" aria-label="Reply to Linda">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I tried this corn bread and it turned out exactly like the picture here and it was delicious and the left overs even more so. </p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-588478">
	        <div id="comment-588478" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2024-12-02T14:35:07-04:00">
                December 2, 2024 @ 2:35 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-588478" data-commentid="588478" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-588478" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I&#8217;m so happy you liked it!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-588545">
	        <div id="comment-588545" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Lois Feltham</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2024-12-04T13:01:34-04:00">
                December 4, 2024 @ 1:01 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-588545" data-commentid="588545" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-588545" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lois Feltham" aria-label="Reply to Lois Feltham">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Made this! Nice and soft. The cast iron pan made a terrific crust. Yes-salty. Use less. I turned down the heat to 425 and mine was done in about 29 min!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-590582">
	        <div id="comment-590582" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Michylle Padilla</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2025-01-20T16:19:57-04:00">
                January 20, 2025 @ 4:19 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-590582" data-commentid="590582" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-590582" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Michylle Padilla" aria-label="Reply to Michylle Padilla">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I baked at 400 degrees for 25 minutes and it came out perfect</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-590864">
	        <div id="comment-590864" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Maria</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2025-01-27T22:12:42-04:00">
                January 27, 2025 @ 10:12 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-590864" data-commentid="590864" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-590864" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Maria" aria-label="Reply to Maria">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>It was a great recipe! The best cornbread I have baked so far. I replaced the buttermilk for coconut milk with a spoonful of lemon juice per cup. It worked perfectly. I liked the nice crust all around the bread. Thanks for sharing it.</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-591363">
	        <div id="comment-591363" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Carol</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2025-02-10T13:43:02-04:00">
                February 10, 2025 @ 1:43 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-591363" data-commentid="591363" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-591363" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Carol" aria-label="Reply to Carol">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I followed this recipe to the tee, even cooked it in a cast iron pan. Unfortunately, it was very dry and I had to throw it away. Very disappointed. And by the way, 1-1/2 cups of buttermilk is 180 grams, not 360 grams. Glad I caught this!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-597205">
	        <div id="comment-597205" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Patrice</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2025-06-01T11:20:38-04:00">
                June 1, 2025 @ 11:20 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-597205" data-commentid="597205" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-597205" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Patrice" aria-label="Reply to Patrice">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Hello! I would love to make your cornbread recipe (it looks so good) for our family gathering in a few weeks. The trick is that we&#8217;ll be at 8,000 ft elevation. What changes would you make to bake this at altitude? Thank you!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-603210">
	        <div id="comment-603210" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Richard Thimlar</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2025-08-03T10:01:20-04:00">
                August 3, 2025 @ 10:01 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-603210" data-commentid="603210" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-603210" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Richard Thimlar" aria-label="Reply to Richard Thimlar">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>I am trying to this today</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-604547">
	        <div id="comment-604547" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Stephen B</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2025-08-23T11:27:20-04:00">
                August 23, 2025 @ 11:27 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-604547" data-commentid="604547" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-604547" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Stephen B" aria-label="Reply to Stephen B">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>At 10,000 feet I increased the buttermilk to 2  cups and reduced the baking soda to  one tsp. I used honey instead of sugar. The result was spectacular. </p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-605607">
	        <div id="comment-605607" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2025-09-08T11:48:50-04:00">
                September 8, 2025 @ 11:48 am                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-605607" data-commentid="605607" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-605607" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Thanks for sharing!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	    <li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-606518">
	        <div id="comment-606518" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong>Michael</strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2025-09-20T21:41:08-04:00">
                September 20, 2025 @ 9:41 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-606518" data-commentid="606518" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-606518" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Michael" aria-label="Reply to Michael">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Can you use a 9 in cast iron skillet with this recipe? </p>
<p>Thank you and have a Blessed day.</p>
<p>Let them now that fear the Lord say, that his mercy endureth for ever&#8221;<br />
 [Psalm 118:4 ]</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    <ul class="children">
	    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-bake1687 bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-607178">
	        <div id="comment-607178" class="comment nopin">

                        
            		
            <div class="post-meta comment-meta">
            	<strong><a href='https://bakerbettie.com' rel='external nofollow' target='_blank'>Baker Bettie</a></strong>            	 &#8212; 
                <time pubdate datetime="2025-09-29T12:12:52-04:00">
                September 29, 2025 @ 12:12 pm                </time>
                
                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-607178" data-commentid="607178" data-postid="30427" data-belowelement="comment-607178" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Baker Bettie" aria-label="Reply to Baker Bettie">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->

	 
	        <div class="comment-content"><p>Yes, you can. Enjoy!</p>
</div>

	        </div><!-- #comment-## -->
	 
	    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
